comment_data.body:
I think the previous version was better because it made it clearer why we were using `.index()` here. With this change, there is no guarantee any more that the types will actually be found in the tuple.

If you want to rewrite this, then we need a different algorithm, basically splitting the possible combinations into separate if-cases:

```suggestion
        if type1.is_pybytes_type:
            if type2.is_pybytes_type or type2.is_pybytearray_type:
                return type2  # bytes or bytearray
        elif type1.is_pybytearray_type:
            if type2.is_pybytes_type or type2.is_pybytearray_type:
                return type1  # bytearray
        elif type1.is_pystr_type and type2.is_pystr_type:
            return type1
```

